President Bush this week declared that a new "axis of evil" - Iraq, Iran,

and North Korea - pose a deadly and unacceptable threat to the United

States. The statement was a significant expansion of the scope of the war

on terror, but there have been few details about how the United States

will deal with these nations.

http://abcnews.go.com/sections/world/DailyNews/axis020131.html


What do you think of President Bush singling out these nations? Share your

thoughts.

http://boards.abcnews.go.com/cgi/abcnews/request.dll?LIST&room=us_SOTU


Plus, documents found in the home of Osama bin Laden's military chief,

Mohammed Atef, spotlight specific U.S. sites, including the Capitol and

Seattle's Space Needle, sources tell ABCNEWS. Were these potential terror

targets?

